So how whatever I could find in the industry is that it is working on a sim to relay co-ordinates. and the accuracy is upto 30meters. (which makes it useless for us)

2nd issue is size. It has to be that small that it fits internally and not externally. bcoz if it is external the fraudsters will get a hint of a foreign object and will be removed physically. With this comes the battery issue. if it has to be that small then it has to take power from the device, which would involve tweaking the device and then regular maintenance of it and to avail a *reliable* technical expert who can actually do the tweak without affecting the device and also be available on a regular basis because it would definitely not b a 1 time job.

Even if we achieve all the above we can do it only after the warranty period of the device has expired because tweaking with the device will automatically lead to warranty expiry. 

If we are doing it with a battery and not allowing the gps device to take power from the source device the battery should last a min. of 35-40 days as the many of us have rental periods for a month or so. I have spoken to several GPS Manufacturers and they did not seem interested.
and neither they had a device that can meet the abv requirements

Samsung smart tag 

And 

Apple air tag 

Worked for us

I tried Jio for Android which doesn't works and Apple apart for being a bit expensive works only with Apple phone which most don't have. Of course the probability of catching someone increases from zero but in the long term it may or may not be worth it until we can have a customised non removable solution
*The point to Address is Fraudsters Sell the products right away making it difficult to track. And police don't help. Nor individually we have time , money & patience. This gives them more leverage.

Like me & Om discussed about all this while we were working on Rento together. We also thought that if we have one agency who is working for all the businesses together we can have a better feasibility of recovery & chance as that Agency/Department work day in & day out is to track and find such fraudsters and get back the products.
This can be done if we have a common point for all the scams that happen who can take it forward this can help.
Exactly, and this could be a Agency with whom we initiate a discussion on behalf of entire community. That way they have workload 24*7. making it feasible to assign some team
Apart from Tracking is anyone aware if this GPS devices can also Shutdown the device completely ? making it useless ? is that a possibility?

One more Idea Om suggested was. *Delivery & Pickup by our team* as a community do you think if we start a Pilot project for delivery & Pickup of all goods by our own logistics team? who also can be trained to do Verifications of all types.

And hence these challenges got highlighted
I feel as a Pilot project for Porter it would be very small. But if we take it as a new team from scratch then it can be done. Just 1 city ilot will prove it
